cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DL 

This paper discusses programming language support for orthogonal persistence, which is a technique for the uniform treatment of objects irrespective of their types or longevity. This topic is closely related to programming languages and software engineering (cs.PL, cs.SE), as well as databases (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), and data management (cs.DL).
